	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64412398">Arrhenius published his paper predicting the consequences of unrestricted burning of fossil fuels in 1894, 130 years ago. His basic predictions of the rate of warming per unit of CO2 added to the atmosphere and that warming would be much worse at the poles have both been borne out.<br> <br>

Scientists started warning us about shitting in our own beds in this manner closer to the invention of the steam engine than to the present, and yet even as climatic patterns go wild a terrifying number of people continue to listen to the comforting lies from big oil's paid liars.</div>
	</div>

